<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-65-1017 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author says there is little cause today for optimism about controllingthe nuclear arms race. The author discusses how both the U.S. and theU.S.S.R. have continually increased their arsenals. The author says itis imperative that we press for maximum possible progress in a numberof important areas: obtain a total freeze, ratify the SALT II treaty,conclude a Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, and begin serious efforts toeliminate the highly destabilizing weapons that are coming along. Wealso need to look at the whole question of the use of nuclear weapons,attitudes about nuclear weapons and whether it is now time to declarethat we must find a way to live in a world without nuclear weapons.</TEXT></DOC>